8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Nanonets and Rossum share a solid foundation of core features including Visual Builder, Code Support, Api Connections, Scheduling. Interestingly, both platforms offer nearly identical feature sets. The difference lies more in the implementation quality and depth of each feature rather than feature availability itself. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Nanonets holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Rossum scores 7/10 overall and 5/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
9:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Nanonets and Rossum offer flexible pricing models. Nanonets has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. Rossum does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
