c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Nanonets is best suited for finance teams, accounts payable, document heavy businesses, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Rossum, meanwhile, shines for enterprises, logistics, supply chain, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, Nanonets describes itself as \"AI-powered intelligent document processing and data extraction.\" Rossum, established in 2017, positions itself as \"AI document understanding platform for enterprise data capture.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Nanonets** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Rossum is a poor choice — far from it. Rossum excels in its own right, particularly for enterprises and logistics.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent ocr and data extraction accuracy, go with Nanonets. If high accuracy on structured documents matters more to you, Rossum is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
